This paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning in a multi-agent setting, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The focus on intrinsic reward and exploration suggests that the paper may fall under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG) or "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of multiple agents implies that the paper may also fall under the category of "Multi-Agent Systems" (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the challenges of applying these techniques to decentralized agents, which suggests that it may fall under the category of "Robotics" (cs.RO) or "Systems and Control" (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.RO, and cs.SY, in that order.
